  "texts": [
    "One limitation of our study is that its results may pertain only to GPT-3.5 and not to other models, due to the causal psychological factors being potentially idiosyncratic to this model or the respective version of the model that we used.",
    "Different models will in general exhibit different behaviours that are sometimes also observed within models at different iterations.",
    "For example, a collection of survey questions -albeit ones that were different from ours -measured that a certain temporal version of ChatGPT was oriented towards pro-environmentalism and left-libertarianism (Hartmann et al., 2023).",
    "If future studies robustly find a certain psychological aspect of ChatGPT to be left-libertarian and the corresponding aspect of other less publicly used GPT-3 models to be right-leaning, our hypothesis for why this occurred would be one of the following.",
    "First, the finetuning and reinforcement-learning selection pressures that were applied to GPT-3.5 -before its public release as the chatbot ChatGPT -may have changed the political leanings of the model."
  ],
